.SH git\-adr\-rm(1) \(en Remove an ADR from git notes
.SS SYNOPSIS
\f[CR]git adr rm\f[R] ADR_ID OPTIONS
.SS DESCRIPTION
\f[B]git adr rm\f[R] removes an Architecture Decision Record from git
notes storage.
This permanently removes the ADR from the notes namespace.
The operation cannot be undone through git\-adr, though the ADR may be
recoverable from git reflog until garbage collection runs.
.PP
Before removing an ADR, the command displays the ADR\(cqs title, status,
and any warnings about linked commits or supersession relationships.
.SS ARGUMENTS
.TP
\f[CR]ADR_ID\f[R]
The ID of the ADR to remove (e.g.,
\f[CR]20250115\-use\-postgresql\f[R]).
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
\f[CR]\-f\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-force\f[R]
Skip the confirmation prompt.
Useful for scripting.
.TP
\f[CR]\-h\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-help\f[R]
Show help message and exit.
.SS WARNINGS
The command warns if the ADR being removed:
.IP \(bu 2
Has linked commits (traceability will be lost)
.IP \(bu 2
Supersedes another ADR (the chain will be broken)
.IP \(bu 2
Is superseded by another ADR (the reference will become stale)
.SS EXAMPLES
Remove an ADR interactively:
.IP
.EX
$ git adr rm 20250115\-use\-postgresql
ADR: Use PostgreSQL for primary database
ID: 20250115\-use\-postgresql
Status: accepted

Remove this ADR? [y/N]: y
✓ Removed ADR: 20250115\-use\-postgresql
.EE
.PP
Force remove without confirmation:
.IP
.EX
$ git adr rm 20250115\-use\-postgresql \-\-force
✓ Removed ADR: 20250115\-use\-postgresql
.EE
.PP
Remove an ADR with linked commits (shows warning):
.IP
.EX
$ git adr rm 20250115\-use\-postgresql
ADR: Use PostgreSQL for primary database
ID: 20250115\-use\-postgresql
Status: accepted

Warning: ADR is linked to commits: abc1234, def5678
Remove this ADR? [y/N]:
.EE
.SS RECOVERY
If an ADR is accidentally removed, it may be recoverable from git
reflog:
.IP
.EX
# Find the notes commit before removal
git reflog refs/notes/adr

# Restore the notes ref
git update\-ref refs/notes/adr <commit\-sha>
.EE
.PP
Note: This only works before \f[CR]git gc\f[R] runs and removes
unreferenced objects.
